  "title": "Assistant Accountant / Senior Accounts & Admin Executive",
  "description": "<p>Job Title: Assistant Accountant / Senior Accounts & Admin Executive<br />Location: Tuas<br />Working Hours: 5 days work 44 hours per week<br />Salary: $3,200 – $4,000</p><p>We are a growing manufacturing companylooking for a reliable and experienced Assistant Accountant  / Senior Accounts & Admin Executiveto join our team reporting to CFO and GM(HR). </p><p>🔧 KeyResponsibilities:</p><p>Accounting:</p><ul><li>Manage partial sets of accounts (AP, AR, GL), with     capability to handle full sets when needed.</li><li>Support payroll, GST submissions, and monthly     financial reporting.</li><li>Ensure compliance with Singapore Financial Reporting     Standards (SFRS).</li><li>Assist with budgeting, audits, and year-end closing activities.</li></ul><p>HR & Admin:</p><ul><li>Handle Work Permit (WP) and S Pass applications,     renewals, and cancellations.</li><li>Oversee payroll administration, leave tracking, and employee     benefits.</li><li>Ensure compliance with MOM regulations and workplace     safety requirements related to HR.</li><li>Support recruitment, onboarding, and maintain accurate employee     records.</li><li>Perform general office administrative tasks.</li></ul><p>✅ JobRequirements:</p><ul><li>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration,     Finance, HR, or a related field.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of working experience, with at least 2 years in the same company, especially     in accounting and Hr.</li><li>Minimum 1 year of supervisory or senior-level experience.</li><li>Proficient in accounting systems and Microsoft Office and     Oracle</li><li>Knowledge of Singapore employment laws, accounting     standards, work pass procedures, and HR-related safety     compliance.</li></ul><p> Salary & Benefits:</p><ul><li>Base Salary: $3,200 – $4,000/month     (excluding allowances)</li><li>Transport allowance</li><li>Annual Wage Supplement (AWS)</li><li>Performance Bonus</li><li>Dental and Medical Benefits</li><li>Insurance Coverage</li><li>Yearly Salary Adjustment</li></ul>",
